apache2-mod_geoip
------------------------------------------
mod_geoip2 is an Apache 2.0 module for finding the country and city
that a web request originated from.  It uses the GeoIP library and
database to perform the lookup.  It is free software, licensed under
the Apache license.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.25-7
  apache2-2.2.6-1
  libGeoIP1-1.4.4-1
  libapr1-1.2.11-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-20060817-1
  cygport-0.3.8-1
  gcc-core-3.4.4-3

Canonical website:
  http://www.maxmind.com/app/mod_geoip

Canonical download:
  http://www.maxmind.com/download/geoip/api/mod_geoip2/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack apache2-mod_geoip-1.2.1-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./apache2-mod_geoip-1.2.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/apache2-mod_geoip-1.2.1-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/apache2-mod_geoip-1.2.1-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

  /etc/postinstall/apache2-mod_geoip.sh
  /etc/preremove/apache2-mod_geoip.sh
  /usr/lib/apache2/mod_geoip.la
  /usr/lib/apache2/mod_geoip.so
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/apache2-mod_geoip-1.2.1.README
  /usr/share/doc/apache2-mod_geoip-1.2.1/Changes
  /usr/share/doc/apache2-mod_geoip-1.2.1/INSTALL
  /usr/share/doc/apache2-mod_geoip-1.2.1/README

------------------

